originalText.text:
I knew I was in good hands as soon as I walked in the door for my consult. The staff was lovely, and Dr. Kwak took time to explain what a revision rhinoplasty surgery would entail. I didn’t feel rushed and he took time to thoughtfully answer all my questions.

The day of the surgery everyone made me feel comfortable and helped to calm my nerves. I could not be happier with my results both in terms of how I look and feel. I’m so grateful with the care I received and would highly recommend.

originalText.text:
It’s been a year since I had upper blepharoplasty and ptosis repair from Dr. Kwak. I’m very happy with my results which turned out exactly how I wanted.

Dr. Kwak is very experienced and patient. He answered all the questions I had and made sure there was no concerns left behind. He gave a thorough assessment on the plan tailored to my needs before the surgery. So I felt very comfortable and trusted that I was on good hands.

The staffs have been very friendly, professional and attentive to communications every step of the way, in every consultation and recovery check in appointments.

I’m very happy with the entire experience and would definitely 10/10 recommend it to those that are interested in blepharoplasty and ptosis procedures.

originalText.text:
Very trustworthy and honest surgeon. I went in for a consultation for lip lift and some concerns about fullness in my lower face. Dr. Kwak and his staff were so incredibly helpful about my options and what the procedures would look like. Unlike many other NYC surgeons, I did not feel pressured into making any expensive or rash decisions.

Again, after seeing multiple other surgeons in the NY/NJ area, I felt Dr. Kwak gave the most sensible and expert advice in terms of addressing what I was hoping to achieve. He was very honest and didn’t push any sort of cheaper or ineffective procedures that would have my face looking weird and unnatural. He offered a much more sensible and effective option about the fullness in my lower face than all the other doctors I consulted with. And from his before/afters on this procedures (compared to other dr’s solutions/results), he’s absolutely right and I trust his opinion fully based on his previous patients’ results.

Since I have a darker complexion, he and his staff were also very honest and informative about which procedures would not be suitable for me in regard to scarring and pigmentation.

After carefully considering my options, I opted to get some simple filler to my chin and was *extremely* pleased with the results. They allowed me to consider the other procedures and when I feel comfortable enough, I will certainly be returning for the other procedures we very thoroughly discussed.

Some of his more intensive services are on the pricier side; but again, facial cosmetic procedures are not something to penny pinch about. Many nyc surgeons claim to be “the best” but Dr. Kwak’s expertise was truly impressive. And the honesty, transparency, and professional ethics that he and his staff presented were truly appreciated and refreshing.

I highly recommend paying him a visit. They will treat you with kindness, respect, and give helpful and considerate expertise. Based on his results, I fully agree that he is the best facial plastic surgeon in the city.

I have been a client of Dr Kwak for many years and will stay loyal to ESKMD for many years to come.
